        "content": "<p>I currently have a directory structure that's something like</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"bp\">├──</span> <span class=\"n\">Cedar</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">│</span>   <span class=\"bp\">├──</span> <span class=\"n\">Difftest</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">│</span>   <span class=\"bp\">│</span>   <span class=\"bp\">├──</span> <span class=\"n\">Main.lean</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">├──</span> <span class=\"n\">lakefile.lean</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>(just the relevant bits). I'm trying to make <code>Main.lean</code> here my entry point for building an executable, and I have this:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">@[default_target]</span>\n<span class=\"n\">lean_exe</span> <span class=\"n\">CedarExe</span> <span class=\"n\">where</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">root</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"bp\">`</span><span class=\"n\">Cedar.Difftest.Main</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>This works fine when there's no namespaces involved.<br>\nHowever I would like my <code>main</code> function inside <code>Main.lean</code> to be within a namespace. As soon as I put it within a namespace though, I get this clang error:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">ld64.lld</span><span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">error</span><span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">undefined</span> <span class=\"n\">symbol</span><span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">_main</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">&gt;&gt;&gt;</span> <span class=\"n\">referenced</span> <span class=\"kd\">by</span> <span class=\"n\">the</span> <span class=\"n\">entry</span> <span class=\"n\">point</span>\n<span class=\"n\">clang</span><span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">error</span><span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">linker</span> <span class=\"n\">command</span> <span class=\"n\">failed</span> <span class=\"k\">with</span> <span class=\"n\">exit</span> <span class=\"n\">code</span> <span class=\"mi\">1</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">use</span> <span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"n\">v</span> <span class=\"n\">to</span> <span class=\"n\">see</span> <span class=\"n\">invocation</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Is there a way to configure the lakefile to accept <code>main</code> inside a namespace? Thanks!</p>",
